    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen completion request returns:\n```\n{\n  -- ...\n  items = vim.NIL,\n  -- ...\n}\n```\nthen request cancellation function errors:\n```\nvim.schedule callback: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/completion.lua:1006: attempt to get length of local 'result' (a userdata value)\nstack traceback:\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/completion.lua:1006: in function 'callback'\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/completion.lua:591: in function 'handler'\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:742: in function ''\n        vim/_core/editor.lua: in function <vim/_core/editor.lua:0>\n```\n\ndue to line\n```\n      if result and #(result.items or result) > 0 then\n```\nnot having a check for `vim.NIL`\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim --clean -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\n`minimal_init.lua`:\n```\nvim.cmd [[ edit a.c ]]\nvim.fn.append(0, \"int main() { r }\")\nvim.lsp.start({ name = 'clangd', cmd = { 'clangd' } })\nvim.lsp.start({ name = 'ctags', cmd = { 'ctags-lsp' } })\nvim.cmd [[ norm! kfr ]]\nvim.cmd [[ startinsert ]]\n```\nAfter launching, trigger omnifunc\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n_No response_\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n* `v0.12.2`\n* `v0.13.0-dev-321+gf83d0b9653`\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nctags-lsp\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
