        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> The implementation does not comply with the specification. It should not return null here.\n\nNo opinion on that, but this:\n\n```\nvim.schedule callback: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/completion.lua:1006: attempt to get length of local 'result' (a userdata value)\n```\n\nis garbage. We need to show better error messages where possible. \n\nWhen a bug like this is reported, \"not our problem\" is not a good enough response, we should AT MINIMUM catch the issue with an `assert` that shows a meaningful error.\n\nThat does not mean we need to handle buggy servers. But it does mean we should `assert` or `error` more meaningfully WHEN we get reports like this which identify cases that users are actually seeing.",
